        "body": "## Summary\n- suppress user-facing cron failure notifications for the exact isolated-runner watchdog timeout `cron: job execution timed out (last phase: tool-execution-started)`\n- preserve the cron run as an error with `lastError` intact\n- mark suppressed failure-notification delivery as `not-requested` instead of leaving it ambiguous\n- keep ordinary cron failures, generic timeouts, webhook destinations, and provider/model failures notifying normally\n\n## Proof\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.gateway.config.ts src/gateway/server.cron.test.ts` — 20 passed\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.cron.config.ts src/cron/service.persists-delivered-status.test.ts` — 16 passed\n- `git diff --check main...HEAD`\n- `pnpm -s lint:core`\n- `pnpm -s tsgo:core:test`\n\n## Notes\nThis intentionally does not hide the cron error from run state. It only suppresses the noisy Matrix/user-facing failure alert for the narrow false-alarm timeout where the embedded agent was already in tool execution.",
